The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      BRIEFS
                  
	Calcutta, April 17: A Class VI student was run over and killed by a truck at Kidderpore this afternoon, following which a mob set ablaze two container vans.     
	The mob also broke the windshield of a fire tender that had reached the spot to douse the blaze. The accident occurred when Sheikh Abdul Karim, 14, was crossing the road on a bicycle. The driver has been arrested.         
	Calcutta: Two persons suffered burn injuries after a fire broke out at a shop in a market at Salt Lakes BJ block. Fire brigade officials said the fire was caused by an LPG cylinder leak.         
	Darjeeling: The Gorkha Janmukti Morcha has decided to ban the movement of government vehicles, including those of police, for an indefinite period starting Saturday. The outfit is demanding the arrest of the Gorkha National Liberation Front supporters who clashed with Morcha activists in the Terai region on Tuesday.        
	Calcutta: The residents of Stephen Court organised a sit-in before the fire-ravaged building on Saturday, demanding permission to enter their homes. Most of the protesters were from Block I of the building, which had not been damaged in the blaze.                                                                                                                                                      
